) regression, all based on data dependent random sampling. Our key idea is that low dimensional embeddings can be used to eliminate data dependence and provide more versatile, linear time pass efficient matrix computation. Our main contribution is summarized as follows. 1) Independent of the results of Har-Peled and of Deshpande and Vempala, one of the first - and to the best of our knowledge the most efficient - relative error (1 + epsi) parA $A
